h3. Summary
After upgrading, Automation or the Customer Notification page shows a spinning wheel and never finish loading.

h3. Steps to reproduce the problem
# Access to the Automation page via *JIRA Service Desk project > Settings > Automation*.

h3. Expected result
The Automation page will be completely loaded and showing all the configured Automation rules properly

h3. Actual result
The Automation page has a spinning wheel which never stop spinning, no Automation rules are shown in the page with error below found from the {{atlassian-jira.log}}
{code}
java.lang.NullPointerException
at com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.automation.internal.configuration.ruleset.dao.querydsl.RuleDao.createRule(RuleDao.java:125)
at com.atlassian.servicedesk.plugins.automation.internal.configuration.ruleset.dao.querydsl.RuleDao.lambda$getForRuleSetRevisionIds$2(RuleDao.java:109)
at java.util.stream.Collectors.lambda$mapping$8(Collectors.java:355)
at java.util.stream.Collectors.lambda$groupingBy$45(Collectors.java:909)
{code}

h3. Diagnosis
The SQL queries below return at least one result:
{code:SQL}
select * from `AO_9B2E3B_RULE` where ENABLED is null;
{code}
{code:SQL}
select IS_SYSTEM_RULE_SET, RULE_SET_ID, ID from `AO_9B2E3B_RULESET_REVISION` where IS_SYSTEM_RULE_SET is null;
{code}

h3. Workaround
Please follow the resolutions steps in [this KB article|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/automation-page-keeps-loading-873922785.html]

