When an issue is deleted from JIRA, the corresponding approvals for that issue are not deleted from the database.

If the user creates a bunch of issues, deletes some of the most recent issues, and then export their JIRA before creating a new issue, after the import JIRA will start creating issues starting with the ID of the most recent non-deleted issue in the export.

Normally this is fine, _except_ if some of the tables don't get cleaned up when an issue is deleted. This can cause issues with approvals where the tables were not cleaned up, so when new issues are created they have approvals left over from the old issues.

